备注 ： ＾

＂＂

闷 公开 □保密 （向校 学位 办 申请 获批 准 为 保 密 ， 年＿ ＿ 月后 公开 ）  

摘要
摘要
血压作为人体最重要的生理参数之一，是反映人体心血管功能的重要生理 指标。目前，临床和家用血压测量通常都是单次测量或间断测量，这种测量方 式不足以反映人体基本生理状况。连续血压的测量则可以实时地连续监测人体 血压，在临床诊断和家庭保健中都具有非常重要的意义。但当前无创连续血压 测量普遍存在操作复杂，需要佩戴袖带，设备昂贵等诸多不便，所以研究一种 更为简便的无袖带连续血压测量方法具有非常重要的实际应用价值。
本论文针对现有基于脉搏波传播时间机制的血压计算模型需要校准、精确 度低等不足，研究了一种基于生理信号多特征融合分析的连续血压计算模型， 通过对同步采集的人体心电信号、脉搏波信号等数据进行滤波预处理，提取了 心电信号、脉搏波信号、脉搏波一阶导数信号以及脉搏波二阶导数信号的相关 特征点，然后根据所提取的特征点计算了初步的建模特征参数。之后本论文在 Pearson 相关性分析的基础上分别建立了基于线性回归以及基于支持向量机回归 的个体化连续血压模型，同时还根据遗传算法关联因素分析建立了基于遗传算 法的个体化连续血压模型，然后本论文将以上三种血压模型进行了比较分析并 从中选择出了建模效果最佳的支持向量机回归模型。实验结果表明，基于支持 向量机的个体化连续血压模型估算的收缩压、舒张压以及平均动脉压的平均误 差和标准差分别为 0.001±3.21mmHg，0.002±2.3mmHg，0±2.4mmHg，并且其相 关系数分别为 0.977，0.975，0.977，比现有文献中基于 PTT 机制的血压模型具 有更小的标准差以及更高的测量精度。因此，本论文所提出的基于生理信号多 特征融合分析的连续血压计算方案具有广泛应用价值。
关键词：无袖带连续血压；脉搏波传播时间；特征选择；非线性建模；支持向 量机
I

Abstract
ABSTRACT
Blood pressure, as one of the most essential physiological parameters of the human body, is the crucial physiological indicator reflecting the human cardiovascular function. Currently, the clinical and home blood pressure measurements are usually single measurements or intermittent measurements, which do not adequately reflect the basic human physiological status. While continuous blood pressure measurement can be continuously monitoring blood pressure in real-time, exerting a great significance in the clinical diagnosis and home healthcare. Owing to the complex operation and inconvenience of the Non-invasive Continuous Blood Pressure Measurement such as cuff wearing and high-pay devices, and so on. Therefore, to research the more convenient cuff-less continuous blood pressure measurement method attaches the vitally significance in practical application.
In allusion to the disadvantages of the blood pressure calculation model based on the Pulse Transmit Time(PTT), such as it needs to be calibrated, low accuracy, this paper studies a continuous blood pressure calculation model in view of multi-feature fusion analysis of physiological signals. By means of the synchronous acquisition of the human electrocardiogram(ECG) signal, photoplethysmography (PPG) signal etc., and preprocessing and filtering process, this study extracted the relevant characteristics of the ECG signal, PPG signal, first and second derivative signal of PPG, then calculated the preliminary modeling feature parameters based on the above extracted feature points. Afterwards, by using the Pearson correlation analysis, this study built individual continuous blood pressure model upon the linear repression and support vector machine regression respectively, and also built the individual blood pressure model upon the genetic algorithm in the light of the correlation analysis of the genetic algorithm at the same time. Then by comparing the above mentioned three blood pressure models, the paper selected the optimally effective model: support vector machine repression model. The experimental results showed that the average error and standard deviation for systolic blood pressure, diastolic blood pressure, and
II

Abstract
mean artery pressure of the individual continuous blood pressure model upon the support vector machine were 0.001±3.21mmHg, 0.002±2.3mmHg and 0±2.4mmHg with correlation coefficients 0.977, 0.975, and 0.977, and it has a smaller standard deviation and higher blood pressure measurement accuracy than the existing literature based on the PTT mechanism blood pressure model. Therefore, continuous blood pressure calculation method based on multi-feature fusion analysis of physiological signals proposed in this paper has broad application value. Keywords: cuff-less continuous blood pressure; pulse transmit time（PTT）; feature selection; nonlinear modeling; support vector machine(SVM)
III

